#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.34/guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Start by implementing `ProtectedResource`:"
msgstr "Comece implementando a interface `ProtectedResource` :"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.34/guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"`ProtectedResource` returns a name from both `userName()` and `adminName()` methods.\n"
"The name is extracted from the current `JsonWebToken`."
msgstr "O método ``ProtectedResource`` retorna um nome tanto do método ` `userName()` ` quanto do método ``adminName()` `. O nome é extraído do `JsonWebToken` atual."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.34/guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Next, add the following REST clients:"
msgstr "Em seguida, adicione os seguintes clientes REST:"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.34/guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "`RestClientWithOidcClientFilter`, which uses an OIDC client filter provided by the `quarkus-rest-client-oidc-filter` extension to get and propagate an access token."
msgstr "`RestClientWithOidcClientFilter` , que utiliza um filtro de cliente OIDC fornecido pela extensão `quarkus-rest-client-oidc-filter` para obter e propagar um token de acesso."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.34/guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "`RestClientWithTokenHeaderParam`, which accepts a token already acquired by the programmatically created OidcClient as an HTTP `Authorization` header value."
msgstr "`RestClientWithTokenHeaderParam` , que aceita um token já obtido pelo OidcClient criado programaticamente como valor do cabeçalho `de autorização` HTTP."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.34/guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "`RestClientWithTokenPropagationFilter`, which uses an OIDC token propagation filter provided by the `quarkus-rest-client-oidc-token-propagation` extension to get and propagate an access token."
msgstr "`RestClientWithTokenPropagationFilter` , que utiliza um filtro de propagação de token OIDC fornecido pela extensão `quarkus-rest-client-oidc-token-propagation` para obter e propagar um token de acesso."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.34/guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Add the `RestClientWithOidcClientFilter` REST client:"
msgstr "Adicione o cliente REST `RestClientWithOidcClientFilter` :"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.34/guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Register an OIDC client filter with the REST client to get and propagate the tokens."
msgstr "Registre um filtro de cliente OIDC no cliente REST para obter e propagar os tokens."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.34/guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Add the `RestClientWithTokenHeaderParam` REST client:"
msgstr "Adicione o cliente REST `RestClientWithTokenHeaderParam` :"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.34/guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "`RestClientWithTokenHeaderParam` REST client expects that the tokens will be passed to it as HTTP `Authorization` header values."
msgstr "O cliente REST `RestClientWithTokenHeaderParam` espera que os tokens sejam passados a ele como valores do cabeçalho `de autorização` HTTP."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.34/guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Add the `RestClientWithTokenPropagationFilter` REST client:"
msgstr "Adicione o cliente REST `RestClientWithTokenPropagationFilter` :"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.34/guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Register an OIDC token propagation filter with the REST client to propagate the incoming already-existing tokens."
msgstr "Registre um filtro de propagação de tokens OIDC no cliente REST para propagar os tokens recebidos que já existam."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.34/guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Do not use the `RestClientWithOidcClientFilter` and `RestClientWithTokenPropagationFilter` interfaces in the same REST client because they can conflict, leading to issues.\n"
"For example, the OIDC client filter can override the token from the OIDC token propagation filter, or the propagation filter might not work correctly if it attempts to propagate a token when none is available, expecting the OIDC client filter to obtain a new token instead."
msgstr "Não utilize as interfaces `RestClientWithOidcClientFilter` e `RestClientWithTokenPropagationFilter` no mesmo cliente REST, pois elas podem entrar em conflito, causando problemas. Por exemplo, o filtro de cliente OIDC pode substituir o token do filtro de propagação de token OIDC, ou o filtro de propagação pode não funcionar corretamente se tentar propagar um token quando nenhum estiver disponível, esperando que o filtro de cliente OIDC obtenha um novo token em seu lugar."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.34/guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Also, add `OidcClientCreator` to create an OIDC client programmatically at startup. `OidcClientCreator` supports `RestClientWithTokenHeaderParam` REST client calls:"
msgstr "Além disso, adicione `o OidcClientCreator` para criar um cliente OIDC programaticamente na inicialização. `O OidcClientCreator` oferece suporte a chamadas de cliente REST com o parâmetro `RestClientWithTokenHeaderParam` :"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.34/guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "`OidcClients` can be used to retrieve the already initialized, named OIDC clients and create new OIDC clients on demand."
msgstr "`O OidcClients` pode ser utilizado para recuperar os clientes OIDC já inicializados e nomeados, bem como para criar novos clientes OIDC conforme necessário."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.34/guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Now, finish creating the application by adding `FrontendResource`:"
msgstr "Agora, conclua a criação do aplicativo adicionando `o FrontendResource` :"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.34/guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "`FrontendResource` uses the injected `RestClientWithOidcClientFilter` REST client with the OIDC client filter to get and propagate an access token to `ProtectedResource` when either `/frontend/user-name-with-oidc-client-token` or `/frontend/admin-name-with-oidc-client-token` is called."
msgstr "`O FrontendResource` utiliza o cliente REST `RestClientWithOidcClientFilter` , injetado com o filtro de cliente OIDC, para obter e propagar um token de acesso ao `ProtectedResource` quando é chamada a URL `/frontend/user-name-with-oidc-client-token` ou `/frontend/admin-name-with-oidc-client-token` ."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.34/guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "`FrontendResource` uses the injected `RestClientWithTokenPropagationFilter` REST client with the OIDC token propagation filter to propagate the current incoming access token to `ProtectedResource` when either `/frontend/user-name-with-propagated-token` or `/frontend/admin-name-with-propagated-token` is called."
msgstr "`O FrontendResource` utiliza o cliente REST `RestClientWithTokenPropagationFilter` , injetado com o filtro de propagação de token OIDC, para propagar o token de acesso recebido no momento para `o ProtectedResource` quando for chamada a URL `/frontend/user-name-with-propagated-token` ou `/frontend/admin-name-with-propagated-token` ."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.34/guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "`FrontendResource` uses the programmatically created OIDC client to get and propagate an access token to `ProtectedResource` by passing it directly to the injected `RestClientWithTokenHeaderParam` REST client's method as an HTTP `Authorization` header value, when either `/frontend/user-name-with-oidc-client-token-header-param` or `/frontend/admin-name-with-oidc-client-token-header-param` is called."
msgstr "`O FrontendResource` utiliza o cliente OIDC criado programaticamente para obter e propagar um token de acesso ao `ProtectedResource` , passando-o diretamente ao método do cliente REST `RestClientWithTokenHeaderParam` — que foi injetado — como um valor do cabeçalho `de autorização` HTTP, quando é chamada a `URL /frontend/user-name-with-oidc-client-token-header-param` ou `/frontend/admin-name-with-oidc-client-token-header-param` ."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.34/guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Sometimes, one may have to acquire tokens in a blocking manner before propagating them with the REST client. This example shows how to acquire the tokens in such cases."
msgstr "Às vezes, pode ser necessário obter tokens de forma bloqueante antes de propagá-los com o cliente REST. Este exemplo mostra como obter os tokens nesses casos."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.34/guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "`io.quarkus.oidc.client.runtime.TokensHelper` is a useful tool when OIDC client is used directly, without the OIDC client filter. To use `TokensHelper`, pass OIDC Client to it to get the tokens and `TokensHelper` acquires the tokens and refreshes them if necessary in a thread-safe way."
msgstr "`O `io.quarkus.oidc.client.runtime.TokensHelper` ` é uma ferramenta útil quando o cliente OIDC é utilizado diretamente, sem o filtro do cliente OIDC. Para utilizar `o `TokensHelper`` , passe o cliente OIDC a ele para obter os tokens; `o `TokensHelper`` irá adquirir os tokens e atualizá-los, se necessário, de maneira segura para threads."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.34/guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Finally, add a Jakarta REST `ExceptionMapper`:"
msgstr "Por fim, adicione um `ExceptionMapper` do Jakarta REST:"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.34/guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"This exception mapper is only added to verify during the tests that `ProtectedResource` returns `403` when the token has no expected role.\n"
"Without this mapper, Quarkus REST (formerly RESTEasy Reactive) would correctly convert the exceptions that escape from REST client calls to `500` to avoid leaking the information from the downstream resources such as `ProtectedResource`.\n"
"However, in the tests, it would not be possible to assert that `500` is caused by an authorization exception instead of some internal error."
msgstr "Este mapeador de exceções foi adicionado apenas para verificar, durante os testes, se `o ProtectedResource` retorna `um código 403` quando o token não possui a função esperada. Sem esse mapeador, o Quarkus REST (anteriormente RESTEasy Reactive) converteria corretamente as exceções que escapam das chamadas do cliente REST em `500` , a fim de evitar o vazamento de informações dos recursos a jusante, como `o ProtectedResource` . No entanto, nos testes, não seria possível afirmar que `o código de erro 500` é causado por uma exceção de autorização, em vez de algum erro interno."

